---
import PageLayout from '@/layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import CTACard from '@/components/sections/CTACard.astro';
import FAQSection from '@/components/sections/FAQSection.astro';
import StatCard from '@/components/sections/StatCard.astro';
---

<PageLayout
  title="PDF to Excel Converter Online | Convert PDF to Excel for free"
  description="Convert PDF to Excel automatically with AI-powered OCR. Handles scanned PDFs, invoices, bank statements, and financial reports. Free online, no signup required."
  canonicalUrl="https://www.formx.ai/tools/pdf-to-excel-converter/"
  showFooterForm={true}
>
  <section class="title-2 bg-f7f8fc">
    <div class="w-layout-blockcontainer pagetitle__container w-container">
      <h1 class="pricing-title">PDF to Excel Converter</h1>
      <p class="section__header__content">Convert PDF to Excel automatically with 99% accuracy, powered by AI. Extract data from PDF to Excel for free online.</p>
      <div class="w-embed w-iframe">
        <iframe src="https://widgets.formx.ai/extract-pdf" style="width: 100%; height: 600px" frameBorder="0"></iframe>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CTACard
    heading="Get started with FormX.ai"
    ctaPrimary={{ text: "Start Free Trial", href: "https://formextractorai.com/signup" }}
    ctaSecondary={{ text: "Speak with an Expert ->", href: "/schedule-demo" }}
  />

  <FAQSection
    heading="Frequently Asked Questions"
    items={[
      {
        question: "How to Convert PDF to Excel?",
        answer: `Converting PDF files to Excel using FormX only takes three steps.<ul role="list"><li class="faq-list-item">Step 1. Upload your PDF files</li><li class="faq-list-item">Step 2. Wait for FormX to convert your PDF files into Excel.</li><li class="faq-list-item">Step 3. Download the Excel outputs.</li></ul><div class="referral-faq-a">The Excel file can then be uploaded to various applications, such as Microsoft Excel, Google Sheets, Quickbooks, Xero, and more, for you to process the extracted data. For more specific use case, <a href="/schedule-demo/" target="_blank">contact our expert</a> to see how FormX can help you automate converting your PDF files to Excel or <a href="https://auth.formextractorai.com/signup" target="_blank">sign up for a free trial</a>.</div>`,
      },
      {
        question: "Why Convert PDF to Excel?",
        answer: `Portable Document File (PDF) is often used to store and transfer information between or within organizations since it can preserve the original formatting and is universally accessible. However, PDF isn't an structured document format, making it very difficult to extract specific data for further processing or automation.<br /> <br />An Excel file, on the other hand, stores the data in a tabular format. Each line of the file is a data record using a spreadsheet. This allows most spreadsheet or accounting programs to perform various tasks on the extracted data.<br /><br />Converting PDF to Excel then allows businesses to extract valuable data from PDF files and transform it into a format that is more much manageable and compatible with different software applications for further processing or analysis.`,
      },
      {
        question: "Is the Extracted Data Safe With FormX?",
        answer: `Rest assured that all your the extracted data will not be used or stored in any permanent storage by FormX in any way. We understand that many of the processed PDF files may contain personal or confidential data. Read our data <a href="/data-privacy-policy/" target="_blank">privacy policy</a> for more.<br />`,
      },
      {
        question: "Is This PDF to Excel Tool Free to Use?",
        answer: `Yes, this PDF to Excel converter is free to use.<br />&#8203;<br />Aside from the free tool, FormX also offers a more advanced solution with pre-built extraction models, or extractor, including receipt, bank statement, invoice, and more. You can also build your own custom extractor with as little as one sample as FormX is powered by machine learning and large language model like GPT-4.<br />&#8203;<br /><a href="https://auth.formextractorai.com/signup" target="_blank">Sign up for a free trial</a> or <a href="/schedule-demo/" target="_blank">contact us</a> to learn more about our Intelligent Document Processing solution.`,
      },
      {
        question: "How does FormX compare to Adobe Acrobat for PDF to Excel conversion?",
        answer: `Adobe Acrobat copies the PDF layout to Excel as a visual representation — data often needs manual cleanup. FormX understands document content, handles scanned PDFs via OCR, and returns clean structured data that can be fed directly into Excel, Google Sheets, QuickBooks, or Xero without reformatting.<br />`,
      },
      {
        question: "What types of PDFs work best for conversion to Excel?",
        answer: `PDFs with tabular data work best: bank statements, invoices, financial reports, inventory lists, price lists, and tax forms. FormX identifies table structures automatically across any layout — including scanned documents — without column mapping or template setup.<br />`,
      },
    ]}
  />

  <div class="section product-section bg-f7f8fc">
    <div class="container-default w-container">
      <div class="product-heading-content-wrapper">
        <div class="product-heading-wrapper">
          <h2 class="product-heading">Make Your PDF to Excel Conversion Intelligent and Automated with FormX</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="product-content-wrapper">
          <div class="_3-block-grid">
            <StatCard number="10x" label="Productivity" description="Replace manual data entry with FormX to automate data extraction and improve productivity by 10 times." />
            <StatCard number="92%" label="Accuracy" description="Our proprietary image pre-processing and OCR result post-processing ensure a 92% extraction accuracy, minimizing the need for human intervention." />
            <StatCard number="6" label="Months" description="On average, businesses can realize the return on investment (ROI) of business automation within 6 months after implementing FormX.ai." />
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="bg-f7f8fc"></section>
</PageLayout>
